In Shi's view, the government chartered aircraft, chartered high-speed rail, send special cars to pick up migrant workers, can alleviate the pressure of enterprise employment in the short term. "But to fundamentally solve the employment problem, we need to deepen the accompanying social reforms so that migrant workers also enjoy the same benefits and rights as local economic development. "

5,412 words, about 10 minutes to read

The fight against the epidemic continues and the resumption of economic activity is proceeding in an orderly manner. However, due to the shortage of personnel, the industrial chain is not smooth, some enterprises have not yet returned to the state of production before the epidemic.

Recently, a number of local governments in Zhejiang Province to "charter aircraft, high-speed Rail, Charter car, " and other hard-core methods to help enterprises back to the field staff. "behind the hard-core practices of local governments in Zhejiang, these areas have faced difficulties in hiring workers and a shortage of workers in recent years, and these practices can be described as 'self-help' by local governments, " said Shi Jinchuan, director of the Zhejiang University.

Wenzhou, one of the worst affected areas outside Hubei, has been repeatedly delayed in the rush to resume work in other parts of Zhejiang. "like the hard-core local governments in Zhejiang, the number of people working in Wenzhou has been declining in recent years, and the repeated delays in starting up in Wenzhou will increase the outflow of labor and may lead to an even greater shortage of migrant workers in the future, " worries many local Wenzhou manufacturing business owners.

In addition to the personnel, the industrial chain is not smooth is the current enterprise to resume work another big problem.

"every industry is a long chain of linked groups of enterprises. As long as the group of enterprises in one link in the chain stops operating, the entire industrial chain can not operate in an orderly manner. " He Lu (not his real name) is the head of a Department of a large petrochemical group, his petrochemical industry is a long-term continuous production, but affected by the epidemic, most of the downstream enterprises are still in a state of shutdown, which led to a large number of petrochemical products full-blown, petrochemical enterprises were forced to reduce production load.

Automobile enterprises are also faced with the dilemma that the industrial chain has not been fully resumed. "We can't go back to full capacity without the upstream component suppliers coming back. We can only provide epidemic prevention materials to the suppliers of the parts and components that are in short supply and help them resume their work so that part of our production line can be resumed, to solve the problem of shortage of epidemic prevention materials for own enterprises and more suppliers.

In this regard, experts urge, to link up good epidemic prevention and resumption of work, as soon as possible to resume logistics, mobility and production activities.

Sample 1:

Chartering cars and chartering airplanes: The joint efforts of government and enterprises to retain the labor force behind the hard work review

Recently, a number of local governments in Zhejiang province took the lead in using chartered aircraft, chartered high-speed rail, chartered cars and other means to help enterprises resume recruitment.

On February 9, the hangzhou-baotou high-speed railway was scheduled to travel to Guizhou and Sichuan for free; on February 16,154 workers from Sichuan were picked up by the special plane from Jiashan County, Jiaxing City, for free. On the same day, the Huzhou city government issued a document: set up not less than 100 million yuan for enterprises to resume work and production subsidy incentive funds, dedicated to enterprises to resume work and production; for enterprises to recruit new employees, give 1,000 yuan per person one-time living subsidies; By the Enterprise Unified Organization outside the City Staff Charter return, charter fees by the full government subsidies.

Zhejiang Tianneng Power Energy Co. , Ltd. ("Tianneng") is located in Xing County, Huzhou, to manufacture electric vehicles for environmental protection power batteries as the main business. The company has more than 1800 field employees, mostly from Yunnan, Guizhou, Henan, Sichuan, Anhui and other labor force provinces. According to the company's holiday arrangements, January 30(the sixth day of the first Lunar Month) company staff back to work. "The outbreak came out of nowhere, many villages were closed and roads were closed, and many of the workers from Yunnan and Guichuan could not return to their posts. " Xu Yuegang, assistant general manager of Tianneng, said the company, as a labor-intensive manufacturing enterprise, it is important that all employees return to work.

On February 9, Tianneng applied to the Changxing County government for a car to pick up employees, and the Changxing County Transportation Bureau took the initiative to dock the enterprise. On February 11, Tianneng successfully processed the first government-designated employee charter pass to return to work in Zhejiang Province.

"while the government was helping US dispatch special vehicles, the company's Epidemic Prevention Command Center also took the initiative to contact the Dehong Dai and Jingpo Autonomous Prefecture Epidemic Prevention Command Center in Yunnan Province. After hearing our request, a deputy team leader of the other side immediately helped us to open the green light of the special line for non-local vehicles in provinces, cities and counties, and to dispatch our buses to the places designated by the staff to get on them.xu Yuegang was particularly touched by the help of the local government.

Employees strong desire to return to work also let Xu Yuegang with emotion. "We have employees in the mountains of Yunnan, where roads are closed and villages are closed, and they can just not go back to work because of the traffic jam, but they have to walk 60 miles to the bus stop in the county town, and it is already night when they arrive. "

On February 14th and 15th buses carrying more than 300 workers arrived at Tenon's factory. "The second batch of eight vehicles will also start to pick up employees from Yunnan and Guizhou, " Xu said, adding that Changxing County had also deployed a large amount of medical supplies to enterprises before picking up migrant workers, help enterprises to do a good job after the epidemic prevention. "Our company has prepared itself for the epidemic and 90 per cent of our production lines are now operational. "

Shi Jinchuan, a local scholar and director of the Zhejiang University in Zhejiang Province, is not surprised that the local government has helped companies resume their work. "The local government should encourage the joint efforts of the government and enterprises to retain the labour force. Behind the hard-core approach of local governments in Zhejiang is the fact that in recent years these regions have faced difficulties in hiring workers and a shortage of workers, and these practices can also be described as self-help by local governments."

Shijinchuan pointed out that after 2008, several traditional manufacturing areas in Zhejiang, recruitment problems highlighted. "In 2008, the new labor law increased the protection of Workers' rights. At the same time, when the financial crisis broke out, the drawbacks of the slow transformation and upgrading of the manufacturing industry in the Jiangsu and Zhejiang regions were exposed. Many enterprises were not profitable, and workers'wages could not naturally be raised by a large margin,"Shi said, under the dual driving of internal and external factors, the labor force in many traditional manufacturing areas of Zhejiang began to appear obvious outflow.

In Shi's view, the government chartered aircraft, chartered high-speed rail, send special cars to pick up migrant workers, can alleviate the pressure of enterprise employment in the short term. "But to fundamentally solve the employment problem, we need to deepen the accompanying social reforms so that migrant workers also enjoy the same benefits and rights as local economic development. "

Sample 2:

Shortage of workers meets epidemic, Wenzhou enterprises worried about increasing difficulties in recruiting workers

As one of the most serious epidemic areas outside Hubei, the severe situation of the epidemic has delayed the resumption of work in Wenzhou enterprises.

"originally, the government said that construction could not start earlier than the 15th of the first month, but it has been delayed again and again. The current requirement is that most enterprises can not start construction earlier than February 18, " said Yu Wenhui, chairman of Deshou Holdings.

On Feb. 11, the newly released power index for enterprises returning to work in Zhejiang Province was 25.97, with the lowest in Wenzhou at 12.25, only one tenth of the normal level. That is to say, Wenzhou enterprises are still in the situation of maintaining the most basic needs of social life.

Yu's company, based in the city of Yueqing, was hit hard by the outbreak. "Our company specializes in the production of PP-R pipe fittings for cold and hot water, PVC-U pipe fittings for drainage and other building hydropower products. In previous years, construction projects began after the Spring Festival, as the construction industry supplies suppliers, around the Spring Festival is our company sales season. But the construction industry has been basically put on hold due to the epidemic, and we are also suffering,"Yu said.

But Yu was more worried about the loss of employees. "Wenzhou is one of the hardest hit areas, with delays in starting work. Given the security situation and the start date, it may encourage some people to stay at home or work in areas where the epidemic is less severe, " Yu said, at present, the company has 120 employees, from Hubei, Guizhou, Sichuan, Anhui and other major labor export provinces.

In Yu Wenhui's view, the end of the epidemic in Wenzhou, or will face severe recruitment pressure.

"On the one hand, Wenzhou has 330,000 people from Hubei, and it is expected to be very difficult for all 330,000 people to get to work in the first half of this year, especially the production lines of manufacturing companies will face great pressure in the first half of this year. On the other hand, the number of migrant workers in Wenzhou has been declining in recent years, as in some hard-core areas in Zhejiang. This epidemic will increase the outflow of labor force, and there may be an even greater shortage of migrant workers in the future,"Yu said.

Since the 2008 financial crisis, Wenzhou "recruitment difficulties" , "labor shortage" and other issues in every year after the news. According to a report in the Wenzhou Evening News in March 2018, the Wenzhou Bureau of Manpower and Social Security selected 200 enterprises from various industries in the city, among which 21 were large-sized enterprises, 56 medium-sized enterprises, 123 small and micro-enterprises and 200 workers were surveyed by questionnaire and on-the-spot interview. The survey shows that there are different degrees of "difficulty in recruiting workers" in the sample enterprises. Among them, the labor-intensive enterprises in our city are most in short supply of ordinary workers. The shortage of ordinary workers accounts for 58.4% of the total number of shortage workers, an increase of 3.13% .

Sample 3:

Difficulty in resuming work in petrochemical enterprises: It is difficult to start the whole industrial chain

In addition to being subject to personnel, the industrial chain is not smooth many enterprises to resume work is another major problem.

On February 14, Haitian Petrochemical Group's production line began to resume. Haitian Petrochemical Group was established in 2000, is a state-level high-tech enterprise, mainly engaged in petrochemical, energy, new materials business, the company's products polypropylene is the main raw material of plastic products.

"Our suppliers have been calling us again and again and telling us that we have to resume production or their machines will be shut down and the consequences will be unimaginable, " said Xie Fei, general manager of Haitian Petrochemical Group, his supplier is a large petrochemical group that produces oil that is the main feedstock for polypropylene products.

Why Petrochemical Group repeatedly urged downstream enterprises to start work?

"The petrochemical industry is characterised by continuous production that can not be stopped, except for three years of minor repairs and four years of major repairs. In addition, 365 days a year, 24 hours a day continuous production. If we stop production suddenly, it will bring huge losses to the company,"said he Lu, a department head of the large petrochemical group, in previous years during the Spring Festival, the company's production of polypropylene raw materials placed in the front warehouse, to be downstream enterprises after the Spring Festival to start work, then to the downstream enterprises supply. "In previous years, there was enough inventory. "But because of the outbreak, downstream companies have repeatedly delayed starting work this year, inventories have not been delivered to downstream companies, production lines continue to ship, and now warehouses are full, and these liquid petrochemical products can not be stacked at will. "

Haitian Petrochemical Group, a downstream company, was shut down on February 1. Xie Fei said, "The company produces polypropylene products that are solid and need to be shipped in containers from abroad. After the outbreak, many transportation lines were shut down and containers could not be transported from the port to the factory. The products we produce can not be delivered to the downstream customers smoothly. There is a huge backlog of products and we have to stop production."

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Under the influence of downstream enterprises did not start, Haitian petrochemical group product backlog serious.

The company, which started work on February 14, also faced problems during the previous lockout. "Although the traffic situation is improving, road and rail transport within and between provinces has not fully recovered, and with few hotels and restaurants opening, drivers are reluctant to make long-distance trips, the product backlog remains high, " Xie Fei said.

Haitian petrochemical group's high product inventory behind, the more important factor is the lower enterprise rework rate is not high.

It is understood that polypropylene as a raw material, can be used in the production of fiber products, manufacturing pipes, cars, parts, pipelines, water pipes, lunch boxes, food packaging, and other industries, including automobiles, construction, home appliances. "Most of the companies that produce these products are labour-intensive and, because of traffic controls, their rework rates are not very high. Coupled with this year during the Spring Festival car sales, construction start, home appliances sales hit larger, the products of these enterprises did not sell out, a large backlog. As a result, these downstream companies are not so willing to start now that they can not consume our products,"Xie Fei said.

In what way to see, and all industries, petrochemical industry chain, as long as one of the chain affected, the entire industrial chain can not operate in an orderly manner. "But petrochemical companies at the top of the chain have to produce continuously, and many downstream companies are now shut down, which leads to problems. "

Domestic Petrochemical Industry Platform Longpu Poly Chairman Zhang Wenlong appeal: "currently, the inventory of polyethylene polypropylene products to be nearly half a year before it is possible to digest, need the entire industry upstream and downstream coordination, so that the industrial chain out of the dilemma. "

Sample 4:

Auto enterprises to save themselves: to provide epidemic prevention materials to the downstream of the industrial chain to resume work

Like petrochemical enterprises, the resumption of work of automobile enterprises is also subject to the industrial chain is not smooth.

Hansheng (not his real name) was on hold from Feb. 7 to Feb. 10, and finally on Feb. 14, part of the company's production line returned to work.

Han Sheng is a well-known car company in China's Middle-level Management, in his view, the current difficulties in resuming work. "although various auto companies have made a lot of preparations to return to work, there are always a lot of constraints leading to the conditions to return to work do not have. Among them, the auto supply chain is difficult to restore all, the shortage of epidemic prevention materials prominent, resulting in many enterprises can not resume work in time."

The difficulty of the auto supply chain recovery is that the industry chain of the auto industry is the longest of all industries. "For example, we have more than 300 suppliers of car parts for passenger cars, and now we have only some parts in stock. If the entire supply chain is not fully restored capacity, even if the car companies back to work, it is not possible to advance all the production lines. At the same time, even if the production capacity of more than 300 suppliers is restored, if the logistics system is not smooth, the production lines of the auto companies can not be fully restored,"Han said, the automobile industry's long chain has decided the industry to be affected by the epidemic situation biggest, the resumption of work is most difficult.

After the resumption of work must also do a good job of epidemic prevention and control, which requires a large number of epidemic prevention materials. "Our company uses overseas sourcing, requesting local governments in the locations of each branch to allocate medical supplies such as masks and protective clothing for the resumption of work, " Han said, at present, the medical supplies raised by the company can only meet the needs of the company itself.

"At the same time, we have to help suppliers to start construction, but we can not help all suppliers to solve the problem of shortage of epidemic prevention materials, so we can only supply epidemic prevention materials to the shortage of parts suppliers to help them resume work, so that part of our production lines can be resumed, " Han said, in order to save itself, the company is currently brewing into the production line of epidemic prevention materials, to themselves and more suppliers to solve the problem of shortage of epidemic prevention materials.

In fact, recently, SAIC-GM-Wuling Automobile, BYD Company, Guangzhou Automobile and many other companies announced the cross-border production of masks. On the one hand, it is to support the fight against the epidemic, on the other hand, it is also in preparation for the normal resumption of work for the enterprise employees.

According to Han, on February 14, the company's Beijing production base after the resumption of production of the first car has been offline. In addition, the current Hefei, Hebei, Nanjing and other bases of the production line is gradually resuming, the company has a third of the production line began to resume work.

But he also said it was impossible for his company to fully resume production any time soon. "The assembly line will not have all the parts in place for a short period of time, and the workers will not be able to return to their jobs immediately. At the same time, there is a lot of uncertainty on the sales side due to the uncertainty brought about by the epidemic. "

In fact, the overall auto industry operating rate is not optimistic. As of February 13,59 of the more than 300 production bases in the auto industry had resumed production, with a return rate of only 32.2 percent, according to the China Automobile Association. Dealers have also announced earlier, 60 dealers group's 3,9974s stores, the comprehensive composite rate of only 8.4% .

EXPERTS: linking up epidemic prevention and resumption of work, to restore logistics and personnel flow

In addition to the self-help of enterprises, how can the government help enterprises to resume work and solve the current predicament of enterprises to resume work?

Xu Qiyuan, a researcher at the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences, said Transport and logistics channels are still blocked and should be resumed as soon as possible. "At present, the contradiction between supply and demand in the market is prominent, and both excess and shortage exist at the same time. Against this background, it is not appropriate for the policy to do aggregate stimulus, but to 'dredge' the relationship between supply and demand. The key to unblock supply and demand is the smooth flow of goods. "

How to strike a balance between effective epidemic prevention and resumption of production while the current epidemic is still developing and specific resumption of work time can not be determined in some areas? In this regard, Xu Qiyuan suggested, to restore the flow of people and Production Activities. "certain technical standards can be given, and based on the number of new cases, the number of population movements, and the epidemic situation of enterprises, clear and quantifiable conditions for the resumption of work can be given to provide reference for enterprises to resume production. In the case of the epidemic has not yet been completely lifted, the local government should also be clear about the post-natal protective measures. "In cases where the epidemic has not been completely eliminated, the government should instruct companies to provide necessary protection to their employees and provide them with adequate market supplies of protective equipment. "
